This orangey, lemony punch is one for a summer party – fresh, light and full of life. Serves 1080ml runny honey500ml freshly squeezed orange juice250ml freshly squeezed lemon juiceZest of 3 lemons 1 x 750ml bottle cachaça – we use Abelha Pour everything into a large jug, stir to combine until the honey dissolves, then double strain into two smaller jugs over lots of ice. Serve in 340ml highballs or wine glasses filled with ice - you should get about 200ml of punch per serving. • João Nobrega, Casa do Frango, London SE1